[SN]TITLE[SN]
Swanage police probe crash driver 'happy-go-lucky'

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A family has paid tribute to a driver who died in a crash that is being looked into by the police watchdog.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Craig Downs, 21, died when his Ford Focus left the A351 Valley Road at Harmans Cross, Swanage, and hit a telegraph pole on Tuesday.
Dorset Police said because a "marked police vehicle was in the vicinity" the Independent Police Complaints Commission had been notified.
Mr Downs's family said he was a "happy-go-lucky lad with the kindest heart".
In a statement, they added: "Nothing can express our devastating loss.
"Craig was loved so much by everyone that knew him."
Mr Downs, from Poole, died at the scene.
